title: If you hate the rain, should you move to San Diego?
description: This visualization aims to demonstrate how San Diego sees the least precipitation when compared to other major U.S. cities.

title: What does the sleeping/estrus pattern for mice look like?
description: These visualizations aim to communicate the sleeping/estrus patterns for mice. But, be careful! One visualization is deceptive. Can you figure out which one it is?

title: Improving the Get It Done App - A Comprehensive Customer Experience Analysis
description: This project focuses on analyzing trends in customer feedback data from a variety of services provided by the City of San Diego to derive insights into what factors lead to positive and negative customer experiences.

title: The Data Science Life Cycle - A League of Legends Project
description: This League of Legends project involved stepping through the various stages of the Data Science Life Cycle; the steps included exploratory data analysis, data cleaning, assessment for missingness, hypothesis testing, the creation of a baseline model and an improved final model, and a fairness analysis for the model. The overall goal of the project was to determine whether either one of the sides in League of Legends (red side and blue side) has a significant advantage over the other side.

title: Understanding the Impact on the Lebanese Population from the 2020 Beirut Blast
description: This project aims to utilize various NLP-based machine learning models to understand the change in the physical, behavioral, and mental effects of the 2020 Beirut Blast on the Lebanese population.

title: A Taylor Swift Song Recommender & Lyric Searcher
description: This project involved the use of NumPy, Pandas, and mathematical techniques to develop a comprehensive Taylor Swift Song Recommender/Lyric Searcher.

title: California Home Price Predictor - A Machine Learning Project
description: This project involved developing a machine learning model using NumPy, Pandas, and Scikit-Learn to predict the price of a California home based on various features like location, resident's age, resident's income, and number of rooms.

title: Which car should you buy?
description: In this project, users are able to input certain criteria they're looking for in a vehicle, and get a good recommendation based on the inputs provided.

title: Predicting the 2020 U.S. Presidential Election Results
description: This project aims to utilize various machine learning models on a comprehensive politics dataset to predict the outcome of the 2020 U.S. Presidential Election.

title: Is it a cat or a dog?
description: A kNN classification model is utilized to predict whether the object in front of a camera is a cat or a dog.

title: Personal Calendar/Task Scheduler
description: This application lets you keep track of your work! Schedule meetings with other people, set due dates, assign tasks, and much more!

title: A Basic Calculator
description: Don't know how to math? Don't worry! Just use this handy calculator!
